content: It helps me to manage the gamut of emotions that I feel on a daily basis.
Helpfull app.

Used it for 4 years and it used to be great. Then I got a new phone and 1) the Backup Restore feature no longer worked and 2) notifications still made an audible sound even when set to "Silent" in the app. I contacted support, but haven't heard anything for two weeks - the app seems abandoned, which is a pity because it did used to do exactly what I wanted.
Good app easy to use but could do with better display output. PDF charts are too small. Unable to restore from backup.
No aftersales support, no password reset option. I asked for support to reset my password weeks ago through email. Haven't heard a thing. There should be a password reset feature.
Everything about the app is excellent... -&- backup/restore from Dropbox works great in newest version. But- Export to PDF doesn't include photos since Feb 2020. Galaxy S9
Really helps track your mood and put your thoughts in a safe little spot
Can't export report
Problem uploading photos. Love the mood and hastag options to see patterns but i have Samsung 9 and cannot save photos to the catalogue. ??? Help please???
Good idea great app

I've been using this app for about 2 months or so now and I really like it. However , there is some kind of bug happening right now; the app is not uploading new pictures for my entries, it replaced the selfie I took with a shot from 4 or 5 days ago. I've had the same picture log for the last 4-5 days, and that aspect is one of the reasons I love it so much. Now it seems to be useless. I've tried contacting for support via the website with no reply. Thanks!
Good for getting a true picture of rapid cycling &/or the efficacy of new meds etc. Captures clear info for an individual, and/or professionals & their clients.

This app is missing several features listed on the app's website. Where's our calendar view, our templates, and charts setting? I bought the app in part for those features, so I'm disappointed that they aren't in the android version.

Love the simplicity and it lets me see patterns. I removed the labels to make it easier to go on 'gut feel'. I also set the colors to go from dark brown, lightbrown/yellow in the middle, to green at the top. To the devs, is there any way to clear old data (but keep recent history)? I took a year break and want to delete all my old history so I can see recent trends.
Insightful
I've been using this app for two weeks now and this is a great app, really precise and helpful. The fact that you can customise everything is amazing.
Ive been using this app for almost four years and I still love it. I can't imagine being without it, at this point.
I wish I could customise more. But it's possinle to edit. I write multiple times during the say if I feel the mood has changed

Update after months of usage: could you please match the features of iOS app? It's good. Although somehow notifications aren't working, and charts seems useless for now. Update after two months of using: history is constantly scrolling to the start, and it's a bug. Charts are almost useless because I have to guess where which day was.

Pretty good app to journal and track emotions, recommended to me by my therapist. A few suggestions: -Make good moods green and bad moods red. It doesn't make sense intuitively that an amazing mood would be bright red and an awful mood would be a positive green color. -Add option to add your own #emotions. Some of my emotions don't come up as default. -Timely reminders pop up at random times, do not follow times I had selected in app.
Easy to use.
Love love love this app. I have bipolar 1 and this app is amazing. It's so easy to use and easy to track my swings. Thank you to whoever's created this. Best $2 I have ever spent.

I dont take selfies, but I find it really handy on this app. I like that I can be as brief or as lengthy as I need. Will be interesting to see if this helps me down the line to be able to look back on this data.

This app may have saved my life? It has definitely allowed me to finally see my thoughts from a different, much healthier perspective. A must have for those who want to change/fix how they internalize experiences.

This is ALMOST perfect. I love how I can set reminders throughout the day, because I forget keep up with mood journals most of the time. Overall, I really like the setup and interface. Definitely worth the purchase. The only problem I've experienced is that sometimes, if I accidentally touch near the back or done buttons, it'll save the unfinished portion, and I can't figure out how to edit it. I'm not even sure if there is an edit feature? That's the only reason I'm not giving 5 stars

I'm enjoying the reminders, the ease of tracking, and the photo journal. It's so much more powerful with the selfies, to provide context and personalization. I wish there were multiple trackers for other health markers in the same app.
I like all the feature's. I just wish it would include a place for med tracking.
Its a good mood tracking app I just wish it had more functions.
I'm a new user so I don't know half the things I can do yet

I have tried many of these apps, and this is the best one. It gives me freedom to write significant feedback, or I can concisely choose a short label if time is running short. My only complaint is that when choosing a mood, the colors don't make sense. Red and orange signify danger, yet those colors represent happy emotions.
Great way to track your moods throughout the day. Would love a way to track individual known symptoms as well, but you can adapt with the hashtag use if you know your triggers and warning symptoms
Can't backup or export.
I Like using this app because It's Easy to use And I always Tell Stories.
Helping me manage my bipolar. Big PP out of big PP

I have had this app for over a month now, and I love it. I have it set to ask me my mood at random times during the day or I enter when I feel it should be logged. I can make a short diary entry with tags. Each mood is on a scale of 1-10 and you can customize the names and colors of the moods. You get 3 scatter charts and your tags become bar charts. Proper tagging is important, but fast & easy. I just wish the time chart was by hour not 3 hours, it would be easier to read.
Ok app for checking in with yourself, noting how you feel. The app then makes a bar graph of how you have felt over a time period.
Excellent app. Wish list: cloud support and access via desktop.
Great app, very easy to use and gives interesting reports to track your moods
This makes charting my bipolar easy! My only complaint is that I can't search for moods, to see when I felt what, overall.
Great app. Does a lot.
Easy to use and helpful
Everything I need to successfully chart emotional/mental fluctuations. Easy to use, intuitive, with helpful features.
Excellent for my bipolar
Nice app
Don't whine
Customizeable Mood scale works great.
Has been very helpful so far!

I was looking for something simple that would let me rate my mood as many times per day as I wanted and this is it. So many apps give you one chance per 24hr period to rate your mood for the Whole day and then demand that you write about it. You can write about how you feel on this app but you don't have to, which actually makes me more likely to do it. Plus you can customize the mood descriptions and the colours. No offense but the colours it come with are gross.ðŸ˜‚

Best mood tracker I've ever used. I love the hashtag system and the graphs that let you see how your mood changes over time. I've been using this app for over five years at this point and it's done wonders for my emotional awareness and self care.

This is a absolutely great app to use... it reminds me to check In on my moods all the time it works great cause I do forget to journal for my Dr. And this app really helps keep chart of my moods. Thanks guys for creating this app!!
not getting any reminders since Q updated

This is hands down the best mood tracking app available in terms of both the ease of journaling and the correlations that are made. Its also has a very good format for the exported data which easily integrates into excel to compare vs other data. Really hope they release the new features available on the iphone version to android soon (map, calendar).

This is a great app! It's user friendly and works as it should. I like that you can choose your own colors for each mood and that you get a chart to see your mood over months and years. It has been really helpful for me! I've had it for two years and I only had to pay 20 SEK for it, which is a very small price for something that works this well.

Really useful. I got this for its random notifications to get a more representative sample of my mood. But it's a bit finicky to set up. You need to go to Reminders in Settings, select a reminder, check "Repeating" and then the random option will appear. I think the random option needs to be more visible.
no meds tracking
Was enjoying this but got a new phone and after all the hours I had spent putting info in to the app I couldn't get it back. Has truly put me off any mood journal app. Disappointed,
Used this on ios for years. Moved to android and all my data transferred from the backup seemlessly. My NHS psychiatrist originally suggested it and she analysed the data.
simple to use. straight to the point

I love how easy it is to use and especially how you can tag certain feelings and look at what prompted those feelings over your history. I also am glad that you can change the colors of your graphs--mine is teal and purple! The main problem I have is that if you set your own reminders to track your mood, sometimes they show up 12 hours off.
Simple and easy to use, great features.
Great mood tracking app
I've only been using the app for about a week now. I wanted a very simple mood tracker and this fits the bill perfectly. Thus far I'm completely happy with it.
really useful!
good work
Nice app
Love this app. great for bipolar, quick and informative customer service. Very much well worth the $ - old mood charts can be transferred manually.
This app was just okay to begin with and now I don't get any of my timed alerts which was part of the whole appeal. Waste of money!
The web site shows that iPhone users are able to set up templates. The Android getting that feature would be super useful.
intuitive to use. nice colour and numerical scale
I can only see the whole period. Why can't i select a certain month to get an overview.
great app for tracking moods and being more mindful of your own emotional state. as a psychotherapist I reccomend it to many of my clients so they can begin to regulate their own moods better.
good for me. Allows me to track mood whilst journalling and using the hashtag system to note things like wake-up time and quality of sleep

Would be better if there was a way to back up data without dropbox. More 
options would be great.
This is a great tool for tracking my mood. Works excellent with Galaxy 9 plus.
I enjoy the app & keeping track of my moods but i feel that it could be improved by saving more imformation & giving me more options
Cant get all the features. cant edit cant add location?
great app would love to be able to sort by tag in app!
Solid app where I can track in my own way but the reminders stopped working

Straightforward app to measure anything on a 1 to 10 scale. I have used for way more things than only mood. Would love to be able to track multiple variables using the scale. it has a small bug where the graph goes back to your first data point, so I have to scroll and scroll just to get to the recent ones. Bit annoying.
Too many steps to enter the photo for a mood. one press to take the photo should accept it and return to the mid entry window. editing should be possible AFTER that

A great app that's super helpful. However, I do wish clicking a previously used hashtag would work to fill it in so you can move to the next one. Currently if I try to do this it autofills but as soon as I start typing it removes the previous autofilled text.
My phone is not recieving the notifications but otherwise great tracher.

I bought this app instead of getting a free one because it says it has the option for random reminders, but I don't see that option. Disappointed bc random entries would control for the effect of time-of-day.
great app, easy to use, will send you reminders if wanted
Very good app , but it comes without the map !! The main reason why I bought it was for this feature:(
This has been vital for me to show to my doctors and to see how well I am coping. The only bad thing is that it doesn't transfer from phone to phone.

Update November 2018. Still using and appreciating the app. Truely free app. 4 yrs now Update November, 2017. LOVE this app. 3 years of faithful use. Makes a valuable record. Has become a quick diary, too. Thank you Devs.
Simple and easy to use! The only thing I wish was that you could edit or add tags.

It's too easy to lose my data. I've used the app for several months but barely have a week's worth of data because changes I made to my phone. I also lost a bunch of data before I realized I had to rename older files. Automatic/cloud backup would make this a 5-star app.
Backup is not working. Got ZipException: Duplicate Entry.

A friend turned me on to this app during a particularly tumultuous period. She thought it might be helpful for me to get a new perspective on how I was handling things, especially once I'd been using it long enough to collect sufficient data. She was right.
Custom notifications are not working.
I love it! I just wish I could categorize the hashtags into feelings and activities.
Cool
Great. I wish you could filter by keyword or specify dates to graph (eg, last month)
The app hasn't been updated in ages and is lagging behind the iOS counterpart. No filtering by date of your mood, for instance. If you haven't started tracking your mood, stay away from this app.
Very helpful in thinking about how you feel each day.

What a fantastic app! Very easy to use, with no ads. U can check your mood 
when ever u choose, and also write a note like a diary in the moment of 
your feeling. Its brilliant!!

I like the tagging system and how it's organized. While writing how i'm 
feeling in the moment, the tags make it super quick and easy to jot it 
down. Then I can review later how certain tags come up with more positive 
moods and which negative moods that help give me an insight to how I'm 
affected overall by certain things. Don't really use the photo aspect much 
but it's a fun fearuee to have. Overall i like the simplicity of the app.

I have chronic depression and I originally thought using this app would bum 
me out by just confirming how bad I feel all the time. But it's actually 
been a good reminder to check in mindfully with how I'm feeling throughout 
the day and assess why I might be feeling that way, and I've started to 
notice which activities correlate with tiny increases in mood, so I can try 
to do those things more often in the future. By no means a substitute for 
therapy/treatment, but I have found it can be a useful tool for applying 
skills I learned in therapy.
Super useful insights throughout my day!
Very simple and practical for my life to track my daily feelings.

One of the few apps I willingly and eagerly paid money for and not one cent 
was wasted! I'm the type of person that regular writing in a notebook just 
doesn't help and is honestly counterintuitive because I feel like I'm not 
meeting expectations of how long or how much I should be writing daily. 
This app provides a good way to track one's emotions and the color aspect 
is perfect because I often identify more with the color rather than the 
letter describing my general mood.

I like using this app. The only little bug I'd like to fix is when writing 
a hash tag, it often doesn't complete even if I click on the predictive 
text - I have to write the word in full and press space. Otherwise, all good

For some reason, the Samsung app doesn't have locations for entries like 
the Apple version did, so I lost all my data about locations when I 
switched. Locations were a fantastic feature, I hope it's added to the 
Samsung app eventually.

Great overall, but the quantitative tags don't work, and it seems to be 
missing a lot of functions listed on the site.

This app is proving to be a crucial tool as a recently diagnosed bipolar II 
sufferer. I had been tracking moods and activity manually, but whilst I 
established a pattern in my cycles over 12 months, got tired of keeping up 
with it. This is quick, easy, intuitive and I set up reminders for several 
times a day when I'm in a 'high' cycle. I have been able to see my trends 
in new, colourful and highly informative ways, providing invaluable insight 
into trends and triggers. A wonderful app... thank you!

Great app captures moods well great that you can take a photo to go along 
with the other information captured

Notifications don't work, layout pretty poor. Will increase of they fix 
notifications.
Do it now is very effective in tracking moods

I just started using this app and so far I'm enjoying it. I like that I can 
set reminders. I'm rapid cycling bipolar and so I'm hoping can see a more 
specific pattern in these cycles

This is a great mood app. You can set up notifications to remind you to 
make an entry. You can take pictures so you can see how you look when 
you're feeling a certain way. You can share it with your doctor. It's a 
great app. If you want to follow your mood, this is the app for you.

Easy to use. Timely reminders. I was hesitant but its work the money. 
Doctors orders.

I've been using this app for quite a while now and I'd love to be able to 
select more than one mood; I've found that I've got mixed states quite 
frequently and end up not using the app because I can't express how I feel 
within the options. I'd be incredibly grateful if you dev could indulge me 
with this new feature. For those bipolar friends out there, THIS is THE app 
you need, no other would let you keep a diary and your own pictures in such 
a neat, unobtrusive and beautiful way. Best tool for Bipolar! ðŸ’– Years 
later, still same relevant points.

Love this app! The hashtags have genuinely helped me understand trends in 
how activities and environmental conditions make me feel.

Works well, easy to use. I would like to be able to customize the date 
axis, rather than just seeing all data

Helpful and looks good Update: this app has been with me through three 
phones. I love it! Thank you.

I've used IMoodJournal daily for the past 13 months. I found it useful in 
gaining a higher perspective on what was going on with my moods, and it 
supported mindfulness practice as I became more skilled at paying attention 
and identifying emotions. One complaint is that as the data set became 
large, the backup function stopped working. I requested help with this 
problem but received no useful response. Also the summary view continued 
showing all the data from the past 13 months. I can't limit the time frame 
to, say, the past 3 months, which would be more relevant. The only way to 
limit the time frame is in an export file. That is how I finally saved all 
my past data - in segments - and saved it elsewhere in case I want to refer 
back. Two days ago I reset the app, deleting all past data on my phone to 
free up valuable memory space. And now I can begin to get a more useful 
picture of recent patterns. Anyone who likes this app and uses it as much 
as I do will probably have to reset it eventually. I did not find the photo 
function useful. I'm stoical (my expression seldom changes from feeling 
great to feeling bad unless I'm interacting with a human who makes me 
smile, laugh or frown) so while it was fun taking pictures, after months it 
became a useless memory suck. Even with these reservations, this app is the 
one that gets used three most on my phone.

I wish you could rate other things as well. For instance, anxiety and 
depression as two separate moods. However, I do find it a useful tool to 
have.
Good enough for me and I tried a couple other free apps before this. Love the Dropbox interface, allows me to keep app over time and many devices.

I really like this app with all the features it has yet being simple and intuitive to use.  What I'd wish for would be a quick mood logging screen when unlocking my phone. There's a time tracker (SaveMyTime) which does that for activities. A quick log when unlocking the phone after a customisable time interval would be little effort for a much closer tracking across the day.  What do you say ? Other than that it's a wonderful little app that helps a lot to get a hold on mood ups and downs! :) The customer support is very nice and incredibly helpful! :)
Good for monitoring my bipolar I and multiple sclerosis.
This app is so useful and customizable! I love it, and it's really been helping :)

Intuitive, attractive and useful; I love it! My one request is that I would like to be able to see an average score for each day, and to be able to view that in a calendar format, to track general trends.
Love the tag feature.  Can be as short as you want it to be.  Simple. Meets my current needs.

Probably the best mood recording app. Especially useful if you experience frequent mood swings within a 24 hour period as it does not automatically use the daily average mood to plot the chart or graphs. Very helpful ðŸ‘ðŸ‘
Basic but useful app

I love this app. It helps me stay mindful and in touch with my feelings. I tried to do this on paper for a long time but I would miss days or not feel like doing it. This app helps by providing constant reminders which I find really useful.
I had been looking for an app that would let me track multiple moods a day. This does everything I wanted it to do! Definitely worth the price.
Easy to use, best mood tracker I've found yet
Fun and useful
worth the money. customizable mood scale and hashtags and all those graphs! plus the option to export to excel and play with the data that way. so great.
Awesome and useful app. Allows you to export your data to PDF, which is great. I highly recommend it. It is the best mood track app I've tried so far.

Pretty much everything is customizable, but the default settings are great for just charting your mood and writing short daily journal entries. I'm really enjoying it and how it's becoming a habit. I'm pushing myself to record three times a day every time I get the notification and it's really helping me stay self-aware and mindful of my mood over time.
It helps me see how I'm doing
Perspective on life achieved

A nice app. Allows me to joint down thoughts on how I'm feeling in the moment. I don't know how I'll use this towards my long-term emotional health but this will definitely be helpful in discovering any negative thought patterns or triggers.
Great app. Wish it had some sleep and anxiety tracking, but can't complain. Very useful.

A couple of days in and I've already noticed interesting patterns. This app is simple and even fun to use, which is amazing for a mood diary! The hashtag and selfie features are unique, help to organize and sift through data, and even see the different moods in your eyes. I'm not into this far enough yet to get much out of the charts, but will definitely keep using it. Thanks!

I really like this app, however, coming from an Iphone background, where the app is free and has more functionality, I wonder when the android version will get them as well. The graph quality seems poor and they don't give you the options to filter the graph by month, 90 days, year as they do on iOS. If they added that for the android version it would be great.
This app is AMAZING! I'm very impressed. It's not the flashiest out there, but I've been using it everyday since purchasing. Exactly what I was looking for. Thanks developers.
Easy to use, quick and simple. I like that there is an option to write a note.

This app is fantastic. I have narcolepsy and so I actually use the app to track my fatigue patterns each hour over the day, rather than my moods. Using tags for different health management strategies (like a power nap) helps me get an understanding of how those factors affect my alertness. Would be good if you could see more Data around tags (I.e. how did I feel an hour later? 2 hours?)
It doesn't show the complete summary. It keeps saying it needs more data but i've been tracking for 6 months. Still no graph
Useful and discreet

Enlightening, fast, simple. The selfie element of this app is really grounding. This app is a convenient way to literally 'take a look at myself' in a private way that is on my terms. I actually use this app which is different then other mood apps I've tried. I like the # feature because it allows me to enter information and identify patterns efficiently on a phone. It takes forever to write dairy entries on a phone and conversely I don't always have a keyboard handy during a mood shift. If I don't record the data at the time I forget important things. I am a moody, bored, impatient programmer who struggles with chronic procrastination of epic proportions. I liked other apps just fine but couldn't stay consistent or find meaningful data that enlightened me enough to keep tracking and look at the results. Nicely done, developers! I have logged consistently for a week!
Easy to use, worth the $2
Easy to track moods and to see them over a period of time. Helpful reminders throughout the day and a good selection of emotions to hashtag at each review.
Easily the greatest mood tracker   Worth the purchase.  Love the customisation and the graphs.
Very easy to use.

So many bugs. The reminders come in at 8am regardless of when I have them set up and I can't export or import backups on dropbox. I can't report these because the "Contact Us" button does not do anything. I really want to like this app but I can't.
This app does exactly what I want it to do! It's so easy to use and I love that I can customize the colors to ones that cheer me up.
This app helps me log my moods and enables me to see fluctuations and possible triggers.
The ux is decent. Adding a bunch of tags can be cumbersome though. I also wish I could add more tap-and-go metrics. It's good, but not comprehensive enough to fly solo.
Versatile and user friendly
Simple, does exactly what it says, and does it well. It has helped me understand my emotions better.
Best app I've tried so far to track and report on your mood combined with a great way to Jornal.   The report format is great.  I'm going to use it to show my doctor and counselor how I am doing.

Still new to this app and really love it.  Keeps me in check with myself and so easy to journal with this vs all the pretty paper journals I buy and are all blank.  Helps my focus with ADHD.  I face and acknowledge my emotions in a health manner.
I like being able to journal about my mood and give multiple updates on my mood throughout the day.
Just started using but I love how it reminds to track.
Happy
This app has helped me to identify my trigger points. Something that has eluded for quite a while.

Excellent app for making some sense of the ups and downs. Also great to have a place to record daily activities, thoughts and feelings. Writing thoughts and feelings down changes the way that you relate to them for the better.
Could have place for mad notes etc
One of many such apps. It feels simplistic to rate *all* your mental, emotional & physical feelings on a single scale & I haven't yet worked out how useful the # values are.

This app is the best of its kind, and I've basically tried them all at this point. There are some minor tweaks I'd make if I was designing my personal perfect mood tracker, of course, but only minor ones - and they're mostly to do with the UI, which could use a bit of an update. It's definitely the best in show, and I'm delighted to finally feel like I've found one I can settle with and stop chopping and changing!
Needs more options

I love the photo integration but I can't find where this app stores the photos. Also, I want to be able to choose the color for each number, not just three. I look forward to adding this to my charts.
The only downfall is having a reminder every 15 minutes. I only like to use it when I feel it is necesary as my mood is generally neutral. But otherwise it's pretty good.
It helps me track my mood throughout the day with helpful reminders!

Great app to use with my therapist.  Helps us to remember to cover everything that's going on in my life.  Features are limited though.  Basically a glorified journal with some gimmicks.  Maybe the charts will be more helpful in the future but you can't zoom in on them and look at specifics.  Just trends.  I get that that is the point but being able to break those charts down a little more might be where they actually become helpful.  4 stars until the charts are more detailed for sure and if any useful features could be added to make this app even better, that would improve the quality and value.  If you are using this with your therapist or find another usefulness to it, great, but don't think it's just goana help you get better or understand yourself better without working at it a little bit.
The fact that you can check in more than once a day is what really sets this app apart from other mood trackers.
This is great for tracking my moods and noting what is going on at the time. Highly recommend.
A great way for me to check in with myself.  A great tool for gaining insight in order to maintain balance in one's life. Thank you. I like balance. :)

This app has helped me and my psychiatric team gain a lot of insight into my moods and triggers. I absolutely love it. I do however wish there was a way to search for a specific tag without having to scroll through like 80 different options to find the one you want. Like I REALLY want that feature, when Was my last period, is it under positive or negative, how do I find it?
Very useful. In particular the reminders and the # option for tracking specifics.
Awesome

Custom reminders are a huge help. Plus you can customize the name of the 1-10 moods to suit your purposes. This app has already made my mood charting more regular and given me useful data. Another great feature: tagging and diary options for each entry. This makes identifying mood triggers easy!
Excellent app at the first glance.  Has great potential.  Hope it gets frequent updates.
I'm glad that I now have it set to 3x a day.  I get a better picture, because when it was only at 3:00, that tends to be my low time and it was a bit discouraging.
Very useful. Particularly the long term graph.
It's a simple app that works well enough to do what is required. I use it daily.

Really neat app that gives interesting insight with the use of tags. Charts & graphs are easy to read & export to keep in a diary/journal, take to doctor appts, use in discussions w/ therapists & counselors, caregivers & family members, even just give a bird's eye view that is a little more objective. Very powerful tool to enable proactive, responsible, honest personal assessment that can be used in conjunction with therapy to maintain quality health.

This is really a great mood tracker.  I can edit when I need to as well as take pictures which is great for tracking moods. I love that it prompts me at specific times too. I even love that if I don't log my mood that shows me something. I don't mind that I initially had to pay bc this is a tool that can help me and my doctors with my mental health. Thank you.
This app is perfect!
Very helpful for tracking moods and changes.
Best mood tracker app I found so far.  Definitely worth the money!
Easy to use
Critical part of keeping myself mentally functional.
Using this whilst going through a mental health crisis - it's helping me to see my moods switching and what is happening when they do
good to keep track of mood n boost activity
This app is pretty good so far
It's a great app to set up tracking your mood.
This app is by far the best!
Great app! I'm using it to help me understand and control my moods, as well as have records for my doc.  Essential for anyone with a Bipolar disorder, BPD, depression, and similar.
Very handy to track how your mood changes over time
I have been using this app for years. I have tried others that were similar, and this has been the best because of the variety of moods. It was also very easy and not time consuming.

Great app, have been using it for over a year. I like the customizability and the tagging ability. The graphs are a great feature, but I wish it was labeled better so I can see what date range is being displayed. I want to be able to zoom in and view my entries from the graph so I can identify patterns and see what was happening in my life at that time. It's really hard to analyze past patterns in the app. I know you cannot export the data but that's a little cumbersome.
It is easy to use.

Updated review:  This is a quite simple but beautiful way to monitor your moods adding text and a pic if desired. Also the color scheme and moods are completely customizable - I added emojis to my moods and made my color scheme pink, blue and lilac.. very pretty!! This is the best mood tracker I've found and I'm so happy with it. I love the customizability (like being able to rename your mood levels) and the multiple trend charts, which are very insightful. The tags in particular are a wonderful asset and I love being able to basically have a journal entry along with your chart. The reminders to "check in" are also useful. Overall a great app for anyone interested in a deeper look into their moods and their  emotional "trends."
Works great my doctor will love this app
And flexible
This is a perfect app for tracking my moods and triggers. It would be an even better app if there was a way for me to edit the different moods colors

doesnt have many options for influence in life or track other factors / feelings.  just ok

Pretty awesome

Nice app

Used while I still had an iPhone, bought on my S5 and works just as well. The graphs are helpful. Love it.

Great

This app has been critical in tracking my triggers for my anxiety disorder, and my kid finds it fun and it makes it a lot easier to help her cope with her own frustrations that come with her ADHD. I highly recommend this to anyone and everyone.
I've struggled with anxiety and depression and this has been helping me track my moods easily to then share with my therapist every week!
Easy to use. Enough options to be useful, but not so many that it is cumbersome to use. Exactly what i wanted.

Well worth the money spent I love it

Good

I like this

great app.

replyContent: Hi John, we have reviewed the app, and think that you tapped Back button while you were entering the description. This lead to opening Capture screen without saving the description. Is this correct understanding? App is updated now to prompt users if they had the description entered and unsaved to ensure they don't accidentally loose data.
